<item>
            <title>[LU-20073] add &quot;SLOW&quot; to review-subtest-change sessions</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20073</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=colmstea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;colmstea&quot;&gt;colmstea&lt;/a&gt;, I noticed on a patch that is adding a test added to &quot;&lt;tt&gt;EXCEPT_SLOW&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; that the subtest is skipped during &lt;tt&gt;review-subtest-change&lt;/tt&gt; sessions as a result.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, I think &lt;tt&gt;review-subtest-change&lt;/tt&gt; sessions are a great place to run a slow subtest, since it can at least run once and probably several times in a dedicated session without affecting the main session.  It would be great if you could add &lt;tt&gt;SLOW=yes&lt;/tt&gt; to these sessions so that the slow subtests are run.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happened for patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/63654&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/63654&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19052&quot; title=&quot;add &amp;#39;lfs find --skip-rebalance&amp;#39; parameter to return a fraction of files for OST rebalancing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19052&quot;&gt;LU-19052&lt;/a&gt; utils: lfs find --skip-rebalance for OSTs&quot;):&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/related?jobs=lustre-reviews&amp;amp;builds=123222#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/related?jobs=lustre-reviews&amp;amp;builds=123222#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/a72e1300-8fb9-4c19-8f8f-049b6538b06f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/a72e1300-8fb9-4c19-8f8f-049b6538b06f&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/62c95970-93f7-4894-97bc-3167fab0b139&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/62c95970-93f7-4894-97bc-3167fab0b139&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/2a9f90bf-ccf3-4b21-83cb-7431dcb0f3eb&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/2a9f90bf-ccf3-4b21-83cb-7431dcb0f3eb&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/9f370f3f-0f03-4873-a662-2593f0e6c4a2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/9f370f3f-0f03-4873-a662-2593f0e6c4a2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
